GLOBAL
Fences: legitimate-looking shops near market edges; they pay 30-50% of
street value and ask no questions; they also sell information
Smuggling: standard approach is false-manifest cargo in legitimate shipments;
inspectors at all five city gates are bribable at different price points
Debt enforcement: criminal networks collect unpayable debts using methods
civil courts won't employ; Red Sand Accounts (Mafdet) converts debts to
maritime-law obligations for harder enforcement
Information brokers operate out of inns, post offices, and temple antechambers
in every city; they sell route intelligence, wanted-person status, and
faction gossip; they also buy it
~
MIDGAARD
The Unindexed Years: missing Containment Era ledgers represent both a
historical cover-up and an ongoing criminal opportunity — certain sealed
records can prove or destroy inheritance claims
Outer ward unlicensed smiths, apothecaries, and brokers exist; Guild
Concordat cannot enforce past the second ring road
Reckoning faction members sometimes trade information about the Breach Tower
contents; approach through the Lantern Registry's unofficial contacts
Gloamvault access: sealed passages below the city; certain criminal
operations use the underground routes to bypass gate checkpoints
~
KOWLOON
Jade Eels smuggling syndicate is so embedded in Harbor Syndic operations
that three Warden investigations were closed without result; believed to
hold a Syndic seat
Violet-marked night markets: sanctioned ambiguity; goods there are legal
but provenance is not discussed; standard fence territory
Salt Court Exiles (Duchess Yuen Ahi): fund debt rings in southern quarter
exploiting founding-house legal flaw; they employ muscle and need deniable
contractors
Ash Cult cells operate in the city; they sabotage floodworks; they have
sympathizers in lower wards who resent the Compact institutions
~
KIESS
Frontier frontier city culture: fewer established criminal networks than
larger cities; most criminal activity is opportunistic rather than organized
Sealed-warrant prohibition in Kiess founding charter creates black market
for Midgaard-issued documentation; forged papers circulate
~
RAKUEN
Black market rations: Garden Ledger controls allocation; hoarding and
resale of rationed goods is common and enforcement is inconsistent
Garden Ledger Clerks' shadow archive of Conclave-era transfer names is a
significant intelligence asset; multiple parties want to acquire or destroy it
Bloom Council "stewardship advisors" who never rotate are the institutional
bottleneck for permits and allocations; they are bribable
~
MAFDET
Jackal Synod: smuggles ritual components from pyramid excavation sites under
false manifests; exploits Quarantine Ledger complexity; connected to Synod
funerary authority networks across the eastern desert
Red Sand Accounts: buy distressed inland debts cheap, convert to maritime
obligations, enforce through Mafdet courts; technically legal, widely despised
Harbor chain goes up every night; ships arriving after dark anchor outside;
goods need to move before dark or wait for dawn — criminal window is narrow
~
